junit.framework
Class SelectionTestResult

java.lang.Object
  junit.framework.TestResult
      junit.framework.SelectionTestResult

public class SelectionTestResult
extends junit.framework.TestResult

A test result which imposes a numbered ordering on the tests which it is asked to run and provides services for selecting and prioritizing (changing the order) running of tests.

Author:
Alex Kinneer

SelectionTestResult

public SelectionTestResult(int[] selectedIDs,
                           boolean displayOnly,
                           boolean countOnly,
                           boolean prioritizing)
Creates a selection test result that selects tests by number.

Parameters:
selectedIDs - Array which contains the selected test numbers.
displayOnly - If true, the names of all the tests in the test suite will be printed and no tests are run. Otherwise, tests are selected and run normally.
prioritizing - If true, the selected tests are collected. A call to runPrioritized() will then run them in the order in which they appear in selectedIDs.

runPrioritized

public void runPrioritized()
Runs the selected tests in the prioritized order, which is taken to be the order in which tests were listed in the array passed to the constructor.

When running in prioritization mode (enabled by setting the prioritizing parameter in the constructor to true), calls to the run(TestCase) method do not run the test, but rather check whether it is selected and store a reference to it if true. The runner can then call this method to run the tests in the prioritized order.

The two passes are required because the design of JUnit is such that we must walk through all the tests first to discover the selected tests. Only then are we able to run them in arbitrary order.
